tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  68,4,"(And lo! thou art) O Muhammad (of a tremendous nature) following a noble religion which is honoured by Allah; it is also said this means: you have great character traits with which Allah has honoured you."
  68,5,"(And thou wilt see and they will see) you will see and know and they will see and know upon the descent of chastisement on them"
  68,6,"(Which of you is the demented) which of you is mad."